Currently Agora.io&#39;s Android SDK does not directly support playing audio on the caller side. This would need to be achieved using Android&#39;s [Telcom][1] package, more specifically implementing [Connection][2], [ConnectionService][3] and [ToneGenerator][4] classes. 

Whenever you start your call you may want to create a new tone, replacing `&lt;AUDIO STREAM&gt;` below with the stream that you want to play the tone within, and replacing `&lt;VOLUME LEVEL&gt;` with an integer (or enum) to set the volume level.

    ToneGenerator dtmfGenerator = new ToneGenerator(&lt;AUDIO STREAM&gt;,&lt;VOLUME LEVEL&gt;);
    dtmfGenerator.startTone(ToneGenerator.TONE_DTMF_0, 1000); 
    dtmfGenerator.stopTone();


For example if you want to leverage the Call tone using the above example, you would use [ToneGenerator.TONE_SUP_RINGTONE][5]

    ToneGenerator dtmfGenerator = new ToneGenerator(ToneGenerator.TONE_SUP_RINGTONE,ToneGenerator.MAX_VOLUME);
    dtmfGenerator.startTone(ToneGenerator.TONE_DTMF_0, 1000); 
    dtmfGenerator.stopTone();


  [1]: https://developer.android.com/reference/android/telecom/package-summary
  [2]: https://developer.android.com/reference/android/telecom/Connection.html#onPostDialContinue(boolean)
  [3]: https://developer.android.com/reference/android/telecom/ConnectionService.html
  [4]: https://developer.android.com/reference/android/media/ToneGenerator
  [5]: https://developer.android.com/reference/android/media/ToneGenerator.html#TONE_SUP_RINGTONE

