&gt; &quot;Given an array of ints, return true if the value 3 appears in the
&gt; array exactly 3 times, and no 3&#39;s are next to each other.&quot;

you&#39;re almost there, however, there are a few mistakes and incomplete implementations:

 1. you didn&#39;t check if the value `3` is next to another value `3` (in which case we return `false`)
 
 2. you return as soon as `count == 3` even though you didn&#39;t search the entire array to conclude that there is no more `3s`.
 3. as it stands your loop condition `i &lt; nums.length-2` doesn&#39;t include the last two elements of the array within the search. 

----------
 solution:

    public boolean haveThree(int[] nums){
           int counter = 0;
           for(int i = 0; i &lt; nums.length; i++){
               if(nums[i] == 3){
                  counter++;
               }

               if(i + 1 &lt; nums.length) {
                  if (nums[i] == 3 &amp;&amp; nums[i + 1] == 3) return false;
               }
           }
    
           if(counter == 3) return true;
           return false;
    }

